[[File:ODocs Fundus.jpg|thumb|oDocs Fundus, a smartphone retinal imaging adapter]] '''oDocs Eye Care''' is a New Zealand social enterprise. It was founded in 2014 by Dr. Hong Sheng Chiong and Dr. [[Ben O'Keeffe|Benjamin O'Keeffe]] in [[Wellington]], New Zealand. The company sought to improve access to eye care by making affordable smartphone-based [[Ophthalmology|ophthalmic]] imaging devices.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.odocs-tech.com|title=Smartphone Ophthalmoscope & Smartphone retinal camera|website=oDocs Eye Care|language=en-US|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref> Their product, ODocs, was publicly disclosed in 2015 when he delivered the message at [[TEDxAuckland]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tedxauckland.com/tedspeakers/|title=Speakers – TEDxAuckland|last=TEDxAuckland|work=TEDxAuckland|access-date=17 June 2017|language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2015, the company won the New Zealand Health Informatics Clinician challenge for the active project category.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hinz.org.nz/page/CliniciansChallenge|title=Clinicians' Challenge – Health Informatics New Zealand|website=www.hinz.org.nz|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref>
